--- log block ---

Upgrading to satellite.js 7.0 causes build errors when building with current Vite version even using its default configs.

## Reproducing

1. Run `npm create vite@latest`
   - Choose any of the framework settings e.g. Vanilla, choose TypeScript
2. Run `npm i satellite.js`
3. Edit `src/main.ts` to add:
   ```ts
   import { twoline2satrec, propagate } from "satellite.js";
   const satrec = twoline2satrec("", "");
   const p = propagate(satrec, new Date());
   console.log(p);
   ```
4. Run `npm run build`
5. Get following build errors:

   ```
   > vite-project@0.0.0 build
   > tsc && vite build

   vite v8.0.10 building client environment for production...
   [plugin rolldown:vite-resolve] Module "node:module" has been externalized for browser compatibility, imported by "/data/vite-project/node_modules/satellite.js/wasm-build/base-release/index.js". See https://vite.dev/guide/troubleshooting.html#module-externalized-for-browser-compatibility for more details.
   ✓ 52 modules transformed.
   ✗ Build failed in 85ms

